title: For Sale:  1896 Finnish M39 Valmet VKT Rare Antique
postcontent: FIRST LET ME STATE CONDITIONS OF SALE: NO TRADES. PREFER NOT SHIP BUT WILL CONSIDER FOR THE RIGHT PRICE. OTHERWISE CASH AND FACE TO FACE ONLY. ASKING $600. #6358X Barrel Date: 1944 - 85% Blue, bright sharp shiny bore, matching bolt, post war stock in excellent condition with a 1896 Izhevsk receiver. Manufactured by famous machine gun barrel maker Valmet. This M39 is an extremely rare legally defined Antique, that has been unfired since being re-arsenaled by the Finnish military. This is essentially a brand new, accurate and powerful rifle that is legally classified as an Antique. Rifle comes with original wartime leather sling. Chambered in 7.62x54R. Only around 100,000 M39 rifles were made. One of the most accurate military bolt action rifles ever produced as they were required to shoot sub MOA. The M39's also have a number of variations and makers/manufactures as well as having quite a diverse history both in WW2 and post war Finland. These are great rifles to shoot and collect. 7.62x54R surplus ammunition is very inexpensive and cheap to shoot - which is a great bonus since ammunition prices have risen so much recently. 7.62x54R is comparable to the 30-06 round, and is much more powerful than its little brother, the 7.62x39 round that is usually chambered in AKs and the SKS. This Finnish M39 Rifle has been protected and preserved for long term storage with cosmoline, which is still on the rifle. When cleaned the rifle and stock will be beautiful. Weight: 9.5 lbs (4.3 kg) Over All Length: 46.75” (118.7 cm) Barrel Length: 27” (68.6 cm) Stock Length: 43.25” (109.9 cm) Groove Diameter: .310” Sight Radius: 22.75” (57.8 cm) Cleaning Rod Length: 24.375” (61.9 cm) Caliber: 7.62x54R No FFL is required to buy or sell antiques across state lines-- they are in the same legal category as a muzzle-loading replica. With no "paper trail”, many think of these as the last bastion of gun ownership privacy.
